<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-14T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="425" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">625.5131/97a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T14:00:00-04:00">August 14, 1937—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>32. We are informed that the Franco-Chilean commercial convention of
                            January 16, 1936, has received legislative approval in France. Without
                            disclosing your interest to the Foreign Office, please ascertain
                            discreetly the legislative status of the convention in Chile.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>